User Stories for Environment Blog
User stories describe functionality from the end user's perspective. Here are some user stories for your environment blog:
Visitor User Stories
As a visitor, I want to view a list of blog posts so that I can browse environmental content.
As a visitor, I want to read individual blog posts so that I can learn about specific environmental topics.
As a visitor, I want to filter posts by category so that I can find content on specific environmental topics.
As a visitor, I want to search for specific content so that I can quickly find information I'm interested in.
As a visitor, I want to view sustainability tips so that I can learn how to live more environmentally friendly.
As a visitor, I want to register for an account so that I can contribute to the blog.
Registered User Stories
As a registered user, I want to log in to my account so that I can access member features.
As a registered user, I want to create new blog posts so that I can share my environmental knowledge.
As a registered user, I want to edit my blog posts so that I can update or correct information.
As a registered user, I want to delete my blog posts so that I can remove outdated content.
As a registered user, I want to comment on blog posts so that I can engage in discussions.
As a registered user, I want to update my profile so that I can share information about myself.
Admin User Stories
As an admin, I want to moderate comments so that I can maintain a respectful community.
As an admin, I want to manage user accounts so that I can handle inappropriate behavior.
As an admin, I want to create and manage categories so that content is well-organized.
As an admin, I want to feature important posts so that visitors see critical environmental information.

